      },
      "lineNbr": 528,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000938
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-10T06:52:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This only clears the state sensors and FRU record set PDRs; what happens to the entity association PDRs then?",
      "revId": "59d86f64465b2cf3bcdf744d3760010f626b24b7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8ba28b50_baaba34a",
        "filename": "host-bmc/host_pdr_handler.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 528,
      "author": {
        "id": 1003003
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-10T11:43:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for raising this. In this flow, Entity Association PDRs are processed differently from State Sensor/FRU PDRs: they are merged into the entity tree immediately when each Entity Association record is received, not buffered in per-fetch pending containers.\nThis patch only moves the previous function-static per-fetch state to instance scope (merge flag + pending State Sensor PDR list + pending FRU Record Set PDR list).\nSo, behavior for Entity Association merge is unchanged by this patch.",
      "parentUuid": "9f079b3d_c3d8ba8a",
      "revId": "59d86f64465b2cf3bcdf744d3760010f626b24b7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
